Title : [Radiological appearances of congenital malformations of the hand (author's transl)].
Date : 1980
Publication_type : Journal Article
Abstract : Pre- and post-operative radiological appearances of various isolated congenital malformations of the hand are described, as observed in a personal series of 52 cases. Six groups of malformations can be distinguished, and are, in decreasing order of frequency: agenesias, syndactylies, duplications, amniotic bands, arthrogryposis, and macrodactyly.
